race.comment: HEY DEMPS (4) doesn't boast the best winning strike rate but ran a nice race last time out, finishing second and beaten only 0.3 lengths over 1609m at Del Mar (Turf) after being prominent at the bend. Finds a suitable assignment and can find winning form. MS BRIGHTSIDE (8) was fresh from a break of three months last start when beaten 2.25 lengths into third over 1609m at Del Mar (Turf). The extra journey should play into her hands. Likely to play a major role. LADY OF POWER (5) disappointed last start when out of the placings over 1609m at Del Mar (Turf), beaten 7 lengths. Finds an easier assignment and can find winning form. TAVOLARA (6) returned from a spell five weeks ago when she was beaten 3.5 lengths into fourth over 1609m at Del Mar. Fitter so expect a better run this time.
